main event: A civilian observed a brilliant orange object in the sky that disappeared and reappeared several times.
interesting points: The object had a contrail, but it was not comparable to that of an aircraft's contrail.
The observers believed the phenomena arose from the effects of an aircraft.
The object's color and behavior were unusual, with the orange color not easily explained.
The sighting occurred around 20-25 minutes after sunset when the sky was still brilliantly clear.
No sound was heard during the observation.
